              "text": "They quickly pick out a whole series of items of the {{u:same type, making a handful of, say, small screws. }} People make extensive use of searching images. One unexpected context is sorting. Suppose you have a bag of small hardware ― screws, nails, and so on ― and you decide to organize them into little jars. You dump the stuff out on a table and begin separating the items into coherent groups. (",
