              "marker": "",
              "text": "다음 글의 주제로 가장 적절한 것은?\nSome people punish themselves when they are under time pressure. They delete all the games on their PC, they stop going for walks, and they don’t spend time with their friends.\nThey then have less pleasure in life and less balance ― and their work performance actually declines. Break out of this pattern by paying more attention to relaxation and getting more involved in living when you are under pressure. Define clear time periods for this: half an hour for a walk, ten minutes to play a game on your PC, and so on. Your mind will become more creative during the break, and you will become mentally fitter. Free time without feelings of guilt will give you the strength to do high-quality work in the remaining time. Furthermore, a certain amount of recreation reduces the chances of developing stress-related disorders."
