              "text": "다음 글에 드러난 Tom의 심경 변화로 가장 적절한 것은?\nAs Tom stood on stage at the school play, he could feel the watchful eyes of the audience. Being in the spotlight made him feel tense. He tried to deliver his lines as best as he could, but he could feel his voice shaking. Suddenly, he realized he had missed a sentence. Without going back, he went on as though nothing had happened. But by the time he finished, his hands felt sweaty and his heart was racing. No one commented on his mistake ― apart from his drama teacher. “Well done,” the teacher said. “Acting is like learning to ride a bike. You may not get it perfect the first time. You may fall off a few times, yet each time you get back on you do it better. Your performance may not have been perfect, but it was great.” His teacher’s comforting words brought a smile to Tom’s face."
